Final Project Report Rubric 
Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing  

Final Project Scope and Rubric 

This rubric applies to the final project in both Introduction to Computer Vision and Introduction to Natural Language Processing. 
 
Students are expected to complete one project aligned with the primary focus of their enrolled course. 
 
Students enrolled in both courses may optionally submit a combined project integrating both domains, but this is not required. 
 
All projects are evaluated using the same rubric, with grading based on clarity of reasoning, appropriate methodology, analysis, and reflection. 

